----------------------
Thoughts for a Wicket like Templating
(Note the JSON as complex data structure)
----------------------

<html>
<head><title>OX - Guestbook Example</title>
<body>
<form ox:bind_to="{ controller : 'root', action : 'post' }">
    <input type='text' name='note' />
    <input type='submit' />
</form>
<hr/>
<div id="posts" ox:type="list.text" ox:bind_to="model/posts" >
    <div class="post" ox:type="text" ox:bind_to="$i"></div>
</div>
</body>
</html>

----------------------
Wicket like Templating + TT as "macro" language
----------------------

<html>
<head><title>OX - Counter::Over::Engineered Example</title>
<body>
<h1 ox:type='text' ox:bind_to='model/count' />
<hr/>
<a ox:type='link' ox:bind_to="{ controller : 'root', action : 'inc' }">++</a>
&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
<a ox:type='link' ox:bind_to="{ controller : 'root', action : 'dec' }">--</a>
&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
<a ox:type='link' ox:bind_to="{ controller : 'root', action : 'reset' }">reset</a>
<hr/>
[% FOREACH num IN [ 100, 200, 1000 ] %]
    <a ox:type='link' ox:bind_to="{ controller : 'root', action : 'set', number : [% num %] }">set to [% num %]</a><br/>
[% END %]
</body>
</html>